GlobalVariables.StudyDescription:
The collection of CDEs used in the Adverse Events/Serious Adverse Events module.
Source Form: NCI FormBuilder: https://formbuilder.nci.nih.gov/FormBuilder/formDetailsAction.do?method=getFormDetails&formIdSeq=4D0BC7DD-57DD-63BE-E044-0003BA3F9857

StudyEventDef.Name: NCI Standard Adverse Event/Serious Adverse Event CTCAE v3 Template

FormDef.Name: NCI Standard Adverse Event/Serious Adverse Event CTCAE v3 Template

ItemGroupDef.Comment: Must be included when this data is collected for reporting.
ItemGroupDef.Name: Mandatory Adverse Event Questions

ItemGroupDef.Comment: There are business rules to indicate situations under which this data element should be used in a CRF.
ItemGroupDef.Name: Conditional Adverse Event Questions

ItemGroupDef.Comment: No requirement for inclusion of this element on the CRF; if the design and scientific questions posed in the study dictate the need to collect this type of data, this is the element to include on the CRF.
ItemGroupDef.Name: Optional Adverse Event Questions

ItemGroupDef.Comment: The following additional elements are optional on a SAE form.
ItemGroupDef.Name: Optional Serious Adverse Event Questions

Question.TranslatedText: Adverse Event Name (v3.0) (Code used to identify the adverse event using a standard mechanism that facilitates analysis. CTEP's code list and associated Category/Term is currently a standard. )
Describe 'Other' Adverse Event (Verbatim AE Description used to 'reinforce' selected AE Type - Code.)
Adverse Event Grade (A coded value to identify the severity of the AE.)
AE Start Date (Date on which the AE was first evident.)
Was patient hospitalized for toxicity? (Normally required only if AE is deemed 'serious'.)
Cycle # (A repeating period of activity involving treatment and rest. Several cycles can make up a course.)
To what is the AE attributed? (List of other therapies surgery, radiation, etc, disease, concomitant meds, other. Select MOST likely.)
Other Attribution, Specify (If 'other' selected in data element above, must provide a - description of the presumed cause.)
AE Stop Date (Date on which the AE resolved.)
MedDRA System Organ Class (SOC)
MedDRA AE Code (CTCAE v3.0) (Code used to identify the adverse event using a standard mechanism that facilitates analysis. CTEPÂ¿s code list and associated Category/Term is currently a standard.)
AE Attribution (This question is not asked for baseline assessments. Question should be asked mandatory for all studies that involve drug therapy.)
Reporting Period End Date (End of the assessment period.)

Were adverse events assessed during most recent period (Indicator to clarify whether any AEs were identified during the - reporting period. This is confirmation that the remainder of the form was intentionally left blank.)
AE Expected?
Serious? (If a 'yes' response is entered, complete the SAE section for - this AE.)
Event Onset Time (Enter the time of day when AE was first evident. Used when Date of Onset is insufficient.)

Course (May be used during protocol therapy period to automatically - set the evaluation start/end dates to the period of the course of treatment e.g. user supplies course# and evaluation period derived.)
AE Evaluation Period Start Date (Date of the beginning start of the assessment period.)
Pre-existing AE? (Should be derivable if you capture AEs for specified periods; not needed if you track an AE until it resolves including worseningrather than for a defined assessment period.)
AE Resolved Time (Enter the time of day when AE was resolved.)
AE Ongoing? (Flag to indicate whether AE has resolved or not. This ensures that leaving 'Stop Date' blank was not done inadvertently.)
Participant Status/Outcome
Adverse Event Condition Pattern (This should be derivable from a review of AEs over time.)
Did event reappear after study agent was reintroduced? (Enter response from choice list.)
Comments (A general comment that should not be specific to a single AE.)
Why serious? (Select the appropriate response.)
Dose-Limiting Toxicity? (Select the appropriate response.)
